claim.claim-text:
1. A wireless repeater for receiving, amplifying and transmitting one or more wireless signals comprising:
a signal processing device for determining one or more attributes of a wireless signal received from a mobile device;
a memory for storing a reference list that includes a list of one or more preferred frequency bandwidths to be amplified and transmitted;
a controller coupled with the signal processing device for comparing the one or more attributes of the wireless signal with the reference list, wherein the controller selects a first active set of one or more frequency bandwidths from the preferred frequency bandwidths based on the comparison; and
a first reception filter coupled with the controller, wherein the first reception filter, responsive to one or more control signals from the controller, filters out signals, communicated to the first reception filter, having frequencies not within the first active set of frequency bandwidths.

16. A wireless repeater for receiving, amplifying and transmitting one or more wireless signals comprising:
a first antenna for receiving a wireless signal from a mobile device;
a signal processing device coupled with the first antenna for determining from the wireless signal from the mobile device, at least one of a frequency of the signal and information indicating a last used frequency band of the mobile device;
a reference list that contains preferred frequencies to be amplified and transmitted;
a controller coupled with the signal processing device for comparing at least one of the frequency of the wireless signal from the mobile device and the last used frequency band with the reference list, wherein the controller selects a first active set of frequency bandwidths from the preferred frequency bandwidths based on the comparison;
a first reception filter coupled with the controller, wherein the first reception filter, responsive to control signals from the controller, filters out signals, received with the first antenna, of frequencies not in the first active set of frequency bandwidths;
a first amplifier coupled with the first reception filter for amplifying signals received from the reception filter; and
a second antenna coupled with the first amplifier for transmitting the amplified signals to a base transceiver station.

23. A method of receiving, amplifying and transmitting one or more wireless signals using a wireless repeater comprising:
receiving a wireless signal from a mobile device;
determining one or more attributes of the wireless signal from the mobile device;
determining a first active set of frequency bandwidths by comparing at least one of the one or more attributes with a reference list that includes preferred frequency bandwidths;
filtering out signals, received by the wireless repeater with a first receiving device, having frequencies not within the first active set of frequency bandwidths prior to amplifying and transmitting.

24. The method of claim 23, further comprising:
determining a second active set of frequency bandwidths based on the comparison of the at least one of the one or more attributes with the reference list;
filtering out signals, received by the wireless repeater with a second receiving device, having frequencies not within the second active set of frequency bandwidths.
